# Project Structure Guide

## Directory Structure
```
src/
├── assets/      # Static assets (images, fonts)
├── components/  # Reusable UI components
├── content/     # Content collections
├── layouts/     # Page layouts
├── pages/       # Route pages
└── styles/      # Global styles
```

## Key Files
- [astro.config.mjs](mdc:astro.config.mjs): Astro configuration
- [content.config.ts](mdc:src/content.config.ts): Content schema
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json): TypeScript configuration
- [package.json](mdc:package.json): Project dependencies

## Configuration Files
- `.gitignore`: Git ignore rules
- `.vscode/`: VS Code settings
- `.cursor/rules/`: Cursor AI rules
- `remark-reading-time.mjs`: Reading time plugin

## Build Output
- `dist/`: Production build output
- `.astro/`: Astro cache directory

## Development
1. Use `npm run dev` for development
2. Use `npm run build` for production
3. Use `npm run preview` to test build

## Best Practices
1. Keep components modular
2. Follow consistent file naming
3. Use TypeScript for type safety
4. Maintain clear directory structure
5. Document complex components
